The AA has predicted that petrol will decrease by 41 cents a litre and diesel by 38 cents per litre. JOHANNESBURG - The Automobile Association (AA) says motorists should expect a slight fuel price drop next month. It has predicted that petrol will decrease by 41 cents a litre and diesel by 38 cents per litre.Illuminating paraffin is also expected to go down by nearly 36 cents a litre. AA s Layton Beard says the strengthening against a drop in international oil prices is one of the main contributing factors. The rand slumped shortly against the US dollar at the wake of Donald Trump s election as next year s president but has regained some of its losses since then. Over the same period, international petroleum has enjoyed the brief rally before heading lower. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)